<h3>Form</h3>

<p>
\{{zz-form}} is rendered as HTML <i>&lt;form&gt;</i> tag and acts as a container for the input fields
of the form.
</p>
<p>
The form component can be bound to a <i>model</i> to support better bindings &amp; validations, it also can get rendered in different layouts.
</p>

<h2>Markup</h2>
<div class="well line-example">
    <pre><code class="handlebars">
        \{{#zz-form form_layout="horizontal" model=someModel action="some-action"}}
            \{{zz-input label="Name" property="name"}}
            other controls here...
        \{{/zz-form}}
    </code></pre>
</div>


<h2>Result</h2>
<div class="well line-example">
    {{#zz-form form_layout="horizontal" model=someModel action="some-action"}}
        {{zz-input label="Name" property="name"}}
    {{/zz-form}}
</div>

<h2>Parameters</h2>
<p>\{{zz-form}} can accept the following parameters</p>

<table class="table table-striped">
    <tr><th>Param name</th><th>Description</th><th>Default</th></tr>
    <tr><td>form_layout</td><td>Can be: default | inline | horizontal</td><td>default</td></tr>
    <tr><td>model</td><td>Can be bound to some model, then every control's <i>property</i> will be bound to the given model's property.</td><td>none</td></tr>
    <tr><td>action</td><td>The action to invoke on the controller when form is submitted.</td><td>submit</td></tr>
    <tr><Td>show_successes</td><td>boolean, if true successes will be rendered per input control.</td><td>true</td></tr>
    <tr><Td>show_warnings</td><td>boolean, if true warnings icons will be rendered per input control.</td><td>true</td></tr>
    <tr><Td>show_errors</td><td>boolean, if true errors icons will be rendered per input control.</td><td>true</td></tr>
    <tr><Td>show_icons</td><td>boolean, if true validation icons will be rendered per input control.</td><td>true</td></tr>
    <tr><td>submit_button</td><td>boolean, if true a submit button will be rendered.</td><td>true</td></tr>
</table>